Pastor Enoch Adeboye, the General Overseer of the Redeemed Christian Church of God, on Wednesday, called for an end to the violence that has trailed xenophobic attacks on Nigerians and other foreigners in South Africa. Adeboye added his voice to the calls for an end to the violence via his verified Twitter handle. He said, “Please shun Violence, its dividends last a lifetime. Let us all embrace peace and remember that regardless of our race, colour or language, we are all of God.” READ ALSO: Xenophobia: African politicians responsible for youths’ miserable situation —Ezekwesili Nigerians and foreigners in South Africa have been the targets of attacks since a taxi driver, was killed in Pretoria last week by a suspected drug dealer. In reprisal attacks, Nigerians have been attacked South African-owned businesses in the country. See tweet: 